  "text": "where ℓ r is a microscopic 'adaptation' length. Intuitively, Eq. (5) means that the local orientation angle of the surface, equal to ∂h/∂z changes at a rate proportional to K II /τ r , with τ r = ℓ r /V . Since the crack is moving at a velocity V , derivatives with respect to z are, for a weakly perturbed crack front, simply related to time derivatives through ∂z = V ∂t. On length scales large compared to ℓ r , one can set the left hand side of equation (5) to zero, and recover [CITATION_1] . In the following, we will assume that the length ℓ r is microscopic.",
